15,01                 00Waterfall

15,01                 00The leaves are nearly all down;
15,01                 00or brown, at least,
15,01                 00a rust mosaic of dirt
15,01                 00and decay covers the land.

15,01                 00The bay is wind-whipped
15,01                 00and dark, empty of boats,
15,01                 00stark in the grim twilight
15,01                 00of fall. On the shore,

15,01                 00in the stall of wind caused
15,01                 00by an outcrop of rock,
15,01                 00we stop beneath
15,01                 00the banded sky,

15,01                 00your hand in mine,
15,01                 00finding that nothing
15,01                 00defines gravity like a waterfall.
15,01                 00We turn to the sky,

15,01                 00the clouds are thin and high,
15,01                 00and the weather grows colder.

